# Blog Web Application with API services

## Project Description

This project is a blog web application that allows users to read and create blog posts. The application uses three APIs to provide additional functionality:

    Google Authentication Service API: This API allows users to sign up and log in to the application using their Google account.

    Messaging API: This API sends notifications to users when there is a new blog post on the application.

    Event Listing API: This API provides updates about upcoming events for blog users to participate if they wish.

## Architectural Design



Installation

To install and run this project, follow these steps:

    Clone the repository: git clone https://github.com/Enemini/myBlogsite

    Install the required packages: npm install

    Create a .env file and add the necessary environment variables for the APIs used in the application. The variables needed are:
        GOOGLE_AUTH_API_KEY: Your Google Authentication Service API key.
        MESSAGING_API_KEY: Your Messaging API key.
        EVENT_LISTING_API_KEY: Your Event Listing API key.

    Run the project: npm start

Usage

To use the application, follow these steps:

    Sign up using your Google account.
    Log in to the application.
    View existing blog posts.
    Create a new blog post.
    Check for new blog post notifications.
    Check for upcoming events.

Contributing

If you would like to contribute to this project, please follow these guidelines:

    Fork the repository.
    Create a new branch: git checkout -b new-branch-name
    Make your changes.
    Commit your changes: git commit -m "Description of your changes"
    Push to the branch: git push origin new-branch-name
    Create a pull request.

